						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Kharapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga III. Year 30: 1207-08 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The damaged inscription is dated in the reign of Tribhuvanavīradēva who is identical with Kulōttuṅga III.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the gift of a lamp to the deity Tirukkarapuram-uḍaiya-nāyanār at Tiruppāṟkaḍal.</p>						

						</summary>
